# 📚 Documentation

This documentation explains the setup, API design, architecture, and decisions for the Finance Dashboard Backend.

---

# ⚙️ Setup Instructions

## 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd backend_finance_dashboard
```

## 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

## 3. Configure Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file:

```env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/finance_dashboard_backend
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

## 4. Start the Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

Server will run at:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

#  API Overview

## Base URL

```
http://localhost:5000/api
```

---

#  Authentication

All protected routes require:

```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

---

#  Authentication APIs

## Register User

**POST** `/api/auth/register`

### Request Body

```json
{
  "name": "Shivam",
  "email": "shivam@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456",
  "role": "admin"
}
```

---

## Login User

**POST** `/api/auth/login`

### Response

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "token": "JWT_TOKEN"
  }
}
```

---

#  Financial Records APIs

## Create Record

**POST** `/api/records`
Access: Admin

## Get Records

**GET** `/api/records`
Access: All roles

Query Example:

```
?type=income&category=Salary
```

## Update Record

**PUT** `/api/records/:id`
Access: Admin

## Delete Record

**DELETE** `/api/records/:id`
Access: Admin

---

#  Dashboard API

## Get Summary

**GET** `/api/dashboard`
Access: Analyst, Admin

---

#  Role-Based Access Control
 Role   -> Access           

Viewer  -> Read-only        
Analyst -> Read + dashboard 
Admin   -> Full access      

---

#  Error Handling

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Error message"
}
```

---

#  Architecture

Controllers → Business logic
Models → Database schema
Routes → API endpoints
Middleware → Auth, RBAC, validation
Utils → Helper functions

---

#  Assumptions

Single-tenant system
Global access to records
No refresh tokens
Categories are free-text
No soft delete

---

#  Trade-offs

Simple queries over aggregation pipelines
No service layer for simplicity
No pagination (performance trade-off)
Basic JWT authentication

---

#  Security

Password hashing (bcrypt)
JWT authentication
Role-based access control
Input validation

---

# Future Improvements

Pagination & filtering
MongoDB aggregation
Refresh tokens
Swagger documentation
Deployment

---

# Testing

Use:

Postman
Thunder Client

